org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.mxml

Class StateDefinition

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.definitions.DefinitionBase
      • org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.mxml.StateDefinitionBase
        • org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.mxml.StateDefinition
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<IStateDefinitionBase>, IDefinition, IDocumentableDefinition, IStateDefinition, IStateDefinitionBase, IDefinitionSet

    public class StateDefinition
extends StateDefinitionBase
implements IStateDefinition
    StateDefinition represents a state in MXML 2009 or later. States are per-class, so these objects are owned by the ClassDefinitionNodes that define classes in MXML.

      • getNode

        public IMXMLStateNode getNode()
        Description copied from interface: IDefinition
        Returns the IDefinitionNode from which this definition was created, if the definition came from the AST for a source file.

        This method may require the AST to be reloaded or regenerated and therefore may be slow.

        More specific definition interfaces such as IClassDefinition redeclare this method to return a more specific node interface such as IClassNode.

        Specified by:
